<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-12-30T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-12-30T05:00:00-05:00" n="914" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d914">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">811.248/823: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Ankara</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-12-30T12:00:00+02:00">December
                                    30, 1942—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 9:46 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1373. The following telegram has been sent to the Legation at Cairo.</p>
                        <quote rend="blockquote">
                            <p>December 30, noon. Your December 29, 9 a.m.<note n="2" xml:id="d914fn2">See <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>.</note>
                            </p>
                            <p>I see no present necessity for sending another B–24 to Turkey in
                                substitution for the Liberator that is damaged at Aleppo provided
                                our Army authorities in Cairo can give me definite assurances that
                                the repairs to the damaged plane will actually be completed within
                                30 days and the plane returned at once thereafter to Eskisehir.<note n="3" xml:id="d914fn3">After being repaired the plane was
                                    returned to Turkey by a civilian crew in March 1943.</note>
                            </p>
                            <p>Repeated to Department.</p>
                        </quote>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>